 I apologize once again for the issues you have encountered. In this case, let me provide a slightly different approach to the XML mission plan that should suit your needs:
```php
<mission>
    <title>Take Pictures and Take CO2 Readings</title>
    <tasks>
        <task id="1" type="Drive">
            <target>[12.345, 678.90]</target>
        </task>
        <task id="2" type="Take Picture">
            <target>[23.678, 456.123]</target>
        </task>
        <task id="3" type="Take CO2 Reading">
            <target>[23.678, 456.123]</target>
        </task>
        <task id="4" type="Drive">
            <target>[23.679, 456.124]</target>
        </task>
        <task id="5" type="Take Picture">
            <target>[12.345, 678.90]</target>
        </task>
        <task id="6" type="Take CO2 Reading">
            <target>[12.345, 678.90]</target>
        </task>
    </tasks>
</mission>
```
This XML mission plan first instructs the robot to drive to one of the trees (the left-most tree), take a picture, and then take a CO2 reading there. Afterward, it moves on to another tree and repeats the process of taking a picture and a CO2 reading for each tree. 